The paper deals with speech emotion recognition using deep learning methods, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of multi-task learning and semi-supervised learning, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Hence, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also uses adversarial training, which is a popular technique in generative models and deep learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with audio data, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
